bib_record.title: Fissions in 32S+184W and 34S+186W reactions at near- and sub-barrier energies

free_txt: For 34S+186W system, the experiment
was performed at the tandem booster accelerator.
For 34S+186W system, three individual
Si(Au) surface barrier detectors fixed at the forward
angles of 35.6, 60.6 and 85.6 degree. Two Si-strip
detectors with areas of 50*50 mm2 at the backward
angles.
No information.
For 34S+186W system, the experiment
was performed at the tandem booster accelerator.
Data from the two strip detectors were
recorded in the coincidence mode with the requirement
that each detector was struck by a fission fragment
and the folding angle between the hits corresponded
to a full momentum transfer event.
The fission excitation function and angular
distributions of fission fragments for 32S+184W were
given.
186W target with thickness about 200 mug/cm2 were
supported by an about 20 mug/cm2 carbon foil backing.
Data were received from C.J.Lin.
Approved by C.J.Lin.
